How can I programmatically create a horizontal line in Qt? I have been able to create a line in the Qt Designer easily, but I want to figure out how to accomplish the same task programmatically. I have attempted to find solutions online and have looked at the xml from the ui file, but I haven't been able to figure it out. The xml from the ui file looks like this:

<pre><code>  &lt;widget class="Line" name="line"&gt;
   &lt;property name="geometry"&gt;
    &lt;rect&gt;
     &lt;x&gt;150&lt;/x&gt;
     &lt;y&gt;110&lt;/y&gt;
     &lt;width&gt;118&lt;/width&gt;
     &lt;height&gt;3&lt;/height&gt;
    &lt;/rect&gt;
   &lt;/property&gt;
   &lt;property name="orientation"&gt;
    &lt;enum&gt;Qt::Horizontal&lt;/enum&gt;
   &lt;/property&gt;
  &lt;/widget&gt;
</code></pre>

To create a horizontal line programmatically in Qt, you can use the `QFrame` class. The line you see in the Qt Designer is actually a `QFrame` with specific properties set to make it look like a line. Here’s how you can achieve this programmatically:

```cpp
#include <QApplication>
#include <QWidget>
#include <QFrame>
#include <QVBoxLayout>

int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    QApplication app(argc, argv);

    QWidget window;
    QVBoxLayout *layout = new QVBoxLayout(&window);

    // Create a horizontal line
    QFrame *line = new QFrame();
    line->setFrameShape(QFrame::HLine);
    line->setFrameShadow(QFrame::Sunken);

    // Add the line to the layout
    layout->addWidget(line);

    window.setLayout(layout);
    window.show();

    return app.exec();
}
```

### Explanation:
- **QFrame**: This widget is versatile and can be used to create lines or frames. By setting its shape and shadow, you can customize its appearance.
- **setFrameShape(QFrame::HLine)**: This sets the shape of the frame to a horizontal line.
- **setFrameShadow(QFrame::Sunken)**: This adds a sunken effect to the line, which gives it a 3D look. You can change this to `QFrame::Plain` if you prefer a flat line.

You can adjust the geometry or add more customization as needed. This code snippet will create a simple window with a horizontal line in it.
